==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[#Latin|Damascus]]'', from Greek ''[[Δαμασκός]]'', from Aramaic [[דרמשק]] (darmeśeq) ‘well-watered place’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/dəˈmæskəs/}}

===Proper noun===
'''Damascus'''
#The [[capital]] city of [[Syria]].

